column4: Dataset S5: A list of honey bee OGS3.2 genes highlighting taxonomic status and caste expression status.

Taxa: Apis = Apis restricted; Apoidea = Apoidea-restricted, Hymenoptera = Hymenoptera-restricted, Insecta = found in Apis mellifera and at least one other non Hymenopteran insect, N/A = orphan gene; Taxonomic status was based on OrthoDB v.6, Waterhouse RM, Tegenfeldt F, Li J, Zdobnov EM, & Kriventseva EV (2013) OrthoDB: a hierarchical catalog of animal, fungal and bacterial orthologs. Nucleic Acids Res. 41:D358-365.

Caste Expression data was obtained from Chan QW, Chan MY, Logan M, Fang Y, Higo H & Foster LJ (2013) Honey bee protein atlas at organ-level resolution. Genome Research 23: 1951-1960.  We used Chan et al's supplementary files, specifically data from their ‘qvsw’ column. Q = queen-biased protein and W = worker-biased protein; NDEG = non-differentially expressed protein; N/A: not present in Honey Bee Protein Atlas.
